    <activity>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Calculate the tangent to this parametric curve. (This is the
          same curve from <xref ref="activity-pc3" />). Choose
          some points and draw some tangents to inspect if they fit
          the curve.
          <md>
            <mrow>
              \amp \gamma(t) = (4 \cos t + \sin 2t, 4 \sin t + \cos 2
              t) \amp \amp t \in [0,2\pi]
            </mrow>
          </md>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          The tangent is the derivative calculated termwise.
          <me>
            \gamma^\prime(t) = (-4 \sin t + 2 \cos 2t, 4 \cos t - 2
            \sin 2t) 
          </me>
          This parametric curve with some example tangents is shown in
          <xref ref="figure-activity-parametric-tangent-3" />
          <figure xml:id="figure-activity-parametric-tangent-3">
            <caption>
              Tangents to <m>\gamma(t) = (4 \cos t + \sin 2t, 4 \sin t
              + \cos 2t)
              </m>
            </caption>
            <image xml:id="figure27" width="90%">
              <asymptote>
                import graph;
                size(12cm);

                xaxis("$x$");
